ould inspect the status and version of openclaw. It’s probably worth reading daily memory files for compliance, looking for today's and yesterday's memory. Let's check if those files exist and proceed accordingly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Gathering upgrade information**\\n\\nI’m contemplating whether to use the openclaw documentation for the upgrade, but I’m not sure if it’s necessary. To proceed, I might need to check the documentation on updating. Inspecting the package.json could be helpful. The easiest way to gather info initially seems to be running a command like `which openclaw`, `openclaw --version`, and `pnpm -g list openclaw`. I might need approval for installations due to network or elevated permissions. A brief progress update might be good before taking action, especially if there's no tool summary.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_sUVJaAUUjCSKmW1K7IhYOtmF|fc_0b2145179fde31c00169ed62b0d628819bb8c9928f21ad1bde","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent/memory/2026-04-26.md","limit":200},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent/memory/2026-04-26.md\",\"limit\":200}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_hO7kjKrsFSga1DM4KGVVYdDU|fc_0b2145179fde31c00169ed62b0d638819b85e9f21450f0c10b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent/memory/2026-04-25.md","limit":200},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent/memory/2026-04-25.md\",\"limit\":200}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"beecode","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":32628,"output":616,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33244,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777164960540,"responseId":"resp_0b2145179fde31c00169ed62a2ecd0819b8482d7de61417ff2"}}
