w/docs/platforms/oracle.md:82:## 4) Install Tailscale\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/oracle.md:85:curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/oracle.md:99:## 5) Install OpenClaw\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/oracle.md:102:curl -fsSL https://openclaw.ai/install.sh | bash\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/oracle.md:108:> Note: If you hit ARM-native build issues, start with system packages (e.g. `sudo apt install -y build-essential`) before reaching for Homebrew.\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/oracle.md:183:This setup often removes the _need_ for extra host-based firewall rules purely to stop Internet-wide SSH brute force — but you should still keep the OS updated, run `openclaw security audit`, and verify you aren’t accidentally listening on public interfaces.\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/oracle.md:200:- **System updates:** `sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade` regularly\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/oracle.md:305:- [Hetzner guide](/install/hetzner) — Docker-based alternative\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/windows.md:2:summary: \"Windows support: native and WSL2 install paths, daemon, and current caveats\"\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/windows.md:4:  - Installing OpenClaw on Windows\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/windows.md:22:- [Install & updates](/install/updating)\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/windows.md:23:- Official WSL2 guide (Microsoft): [https://learn.microsoft.com/windows/wsl/install](https://learn.microsoft.com/windows/wsl/install)\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/windows.md:31:- website installer via `install.ps1`\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/windows.md:42:- `openclaw onboard --non-interactive --install-daemon` and `openclaw gateway install` try Windows Scheduled Tasks first\n/Users/ling/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emn