bility │ 2 notices · 1 plugin                                                                          │\n│ Probes               │ skipped (use --deep)                                                                          │\n│ Events               │ none                                                                                          │\n│ Tasks                │ 0 active · 0 queued · 0 running · 14 issues · audit 130 warn · 195 tracked                    │\n│ Heartbeat            │ 30m (main), disabled (backup), disabled (coder-lite), disabled (coding-agent), disabled       │\n│                      │ (downloader), disabled (simple), disabled (tester), disabled (xiaoguanjia)                    │\n│ Sessions             │ 45 active · default deepseek-v4-flash (131k ctx) · 8 stores                                   │\n└──────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nPlugin compatibility\n  WARN active-task-guard still uses legacy before_agent_start; keep regression coverage on this plugin, and prefer before_model_resolve/before_prompt_build for new work.\n  INFO active-task-guard is hook-only. This remains a supported compatibility path, but it has not migrated to explicit capability registration yet.\n\nSecurity audit\nSummary: 5 critical · 6 warn · 1 info\n  CRITICAL Open groupPolicy with elevated tools enabled\n    Found groupPolicy=\"open\" at: - channels.feishu.groupPolicy - channels.feishu.accounts.default.groupPolicy With tools.elevated enabled, a prompt injection in th…\n    Fix: Set groupPolicy=\"allowlist\" and keep elevated allowlists extremely tight.\n  CRITICAL Open groupPolicy with runtime/filesystem tools exposed\n    Found groupPolicy=\"open\" at: - channels.feishu.groupPolicy - channels.feishu.accounts.default.groupPolicy Risky tool exposure contexts: - agents.defaults (sand…\n    Fix: For open groups, prefer tools.profile=\"messaging\" (or deny group:runtime/group:fs